description:
28th June 2015 22:40 to 01:00 BBC2 HD

The third and final night of BBC Two's coverage of Glastonbury and presenters Jo Whiley and Mark Radcliffe introduce highlights from the last day of the festival, including mod legends The Who headlining the Pyramid Stage as they make a welcome return to Glastonbury Festival to celebrate their 50th anniversary. Plus highlights from F.F.S. (the unique collaboration of Franz Ferdinand and Sparks), Paul Weller and Ryan Adams. Also some special acoustic performances from the BBC Two bird's-eye view studio and a fond look back at the highlights of the Glastonbury Festival weekend of 2015.
